The PicoAir enclosure was designed in OnShape and measures 90 × 60 × 65mm — roughly the size of a small speaker, compact enough for any desk.

Key design decisions:

Two hexagonal mesh grilles on the front face allow proper airflow to both the MQ135 and DHT22 sensors
A 0.96 inch OLED window at the top displays live readings
An RGB LED diffuser hole sits center front for the air quality color indicator
Rear vent slots allow heat from the MQ135 internal heater to escape
A 10 degree angled base tilts the face toward the user for easy reading
Single USB cable powers everything — no separate power supply needed
